1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper discusses a new architecture for time of flight cameras, which are commonly used in computer vision applications for depth sensing. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): Time of flight cameras are also commonly used in robotics for obstacle detection and navigation. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the encoding of distance information using frequency, which is related to information theory. 
4. cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper discusses the use of frequency-domain techniques for time of flight sensing, which is related to signal processing. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): Time of flight cameras are also used in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality.
